  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Inclusion criteria

               1. Pediatric patient undergoing scheduled major surgery which require continuous
                  arterial pressure monitoring

               2. Term neonates and children &lt; 4 years old weighing &gt;/= 3 kg and &lt; 12 kg

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Exclusion criteria

               1. Patients with a skin wound or infection around puncture site

               2. Abnormal circulation in the hand (known vascular compromise, mottling, cool skin
                  temp relative to other hand, poor capillary refill)

               3. Recent radial arterial puncture (less than 1 month)

               4. Any emergency surgery or profound hemodynamic instability requiring urgent
                  arterial cannulation.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
